<subSubSection pageNumber="617" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="617">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">Note:</emphasis>
Reveal (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">Taxon</emphasis>
38: 516. 1989), regarding Smith (1812) as having typified the name on 115.3 (LINN), a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Elliot" authorityName="Elliot" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cistaceae" genus="Lechea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">L. villosa</emphasis>
Elliot
</taxonomicName>
, proposed the name for conservation with 115.5 (LINN) as conserved type. However, the Committee for Spermatophyta decided (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">Taxon</emphasis>
42: 694. 1993) that Smith had not made an effective typification, but that Britton (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">l.c.</emphasis>
) had done so, using 115.5 (LINN). As this is identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cistaceae" genus="Lechea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="617">L. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of usage, the proposal was declined as unnecessary.
</paragraph>
